'''[[exponential]] [[growth]]'''
#The growth in the [[value]] of a [[quantity]], in which the [[rate]] of growth is [[proportional]] to the [[instantaneous]] value of the quantity. i.e. when the value has doubled, the rate of increase will also have doubled. The rate may be [[positive]] or [[negative]].
#*Note: The use of this phrase to mean [[rapid]] growth is incorrect.